The paper deals with tuning a numerical library for dense QR factorization on multicore architectures. This involves optimizing the performance of algorithms on hardware systems, which falls under the category of computer science and mathematics (cs.MS). The paper also discusses the challenges of modeling and forecasting algorithm behavior on modern multicore machines, which could be relevant to performance modeling and prediction (cs.PF). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing algorithms for parallel computing, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of empirical methods for tuning, which could be relevant to the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AR). Finally, the paper involves numerical optimization, which could fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
